2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 CRIMINAL JUSTICE AND PUBLIC SAFETY
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Clerk of the House.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1294, L.D. 1933, “An Act to Require
10 Law Enforcement Officers Employed by Tribal Governments to Complete the Same
11 Training Required for Other Law Enforcement Officers”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, to Study Pathways for Tribal Law Enforcement Officers to Receive a
14 Waiver for the Maine Criminal Justice Academy Basic Law Enforcement Training
15 Requirement'
16 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
17 'Sec. 1. Maine Criminal Justice Academy to convene working group.
18 Resolved: That the Director of the Maine Criminal Justice Academy, pursuant to the
19 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 25, section 2804-A, shall convene a working group that
20 includes representatives from each federally recognized Indian nation, tribe or band in the
21 State that employs tribal law enforcement officers. The working group shall study the
22 eligibility of tribal law enforcement officers who have received training from the United
23 States Department of the Interior, Bureau of Indian Affairs, Indian Police Academy to
24 receive a waiver for the Maine Criminal Justice Academy's basic law enforcement training
25 requirements under Title 25, section 2804-C.
26 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That, by January 1, 2026, the Director of the Maine
27 Criminal Justice Academy shall submit a report that includes the findings and
28 recommendations of the working group under section 1, including suggested legislation, to
29 the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety. The committee may
30 submit legislation based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd
31 Legislature.'
32 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
33 number to read consecutively.
