COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1294, L.D. 1933
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment directs the Director
33 of the Maine Criminal Justice Academy to convene a working group that includes
44 representatives from each federally recognized Indian nation, tribe or band in the State that
55 has law enforcement officers to study the eligibility of certain tribal law enforcement
66 officers to receive waivers for the academy's basic law enforcement training requirements.
77 The academy is required to submit a report by January 1, 2026 to the Joint Standing
88 Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety, which may submit legislation based on
99 the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
